Why CC BY 4.0 for the specification?
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The OpenAPI spec is intended to be a vendor-neutral, industry-wide
contract. CC BY 4.0 is the most permissive license that still requires
downstream users to attribute the standard's origin — preventing silent
forks while encouraging broad adoption (banks, certification bodies,
NGOs, competitors, governments).

